Description: Upper body sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, an amphora or oinochoe; exterior: dark grey slip and graffito inscription.
Curator's comments: According to Gardner (1888 pl. XXII, no. 840), the sherd belongs with but does not join British Museum 1888,0601.620, which is very plausible.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.017)
